# Forepath Nx Generators

Use this skill when adding new applications, domain libraries, domains, MCP servers, Keycloak themes, desktop apps, or agent-context wiring in this monorepo.

## Guardrails (non-negotiable)

- **Generators first:** Use `@forepath/code` and `@forepath/ai` generators. Do **not** hand-create `project.json`, `apps/` trees, or `libs/domains/` layout when a generator exists
- **Schema is source of truth:** Read `tools/code/src/generators/<name>/schema.json` (or `tools/ai/src/generators/<name>/schema.json`) before choosing flags. Do not guess option names from memory
- **Domain before apps:** If the target domain folder does not exist under `apps/<domain>/` or `libs/domains/<domain>/`, run `@forepath/code:domain` first
- **Respect boundaries:** Generators set Nx tags (`domain:*`, `scope:*`, `type:*`) and update `.eslintrc.json` / `tsconfig.base.json`. Do not bypass tags to wire forbidden imports
- **Capture output once:** When running generators from the shell, follow **`nx-cli.mdc`** — persist logs under `tmp/nx-agent/` and read buffers instead of re-running to inspect output
- **No programmatic scaffolding:** `@forepath/code` exposes generators only; use `nx generate`, not copied templates from other projects

## Packages

| Package | Role | Invoke as |
|---------|------|-----------|
| `@forepath/code` | Apps, domains, domain libraries, MCP, Keycloak themes, Electron natives, repo init | `nx generate @forepath/code:<generator>` |
| `@forepath/ai` | Validate/transform `.agenstra/` agent context | `nx generate @forepath/ai:context` or `nx run <project>:agenstra-transform` |

Reference READMEs: `tools/code/README.md`, `tools/ai/README.md`.

## Naming and layout (what generators produce)

**Applications** (via `backend`, `frontend`, `native`, `mcp`, `keycloak-theme`):

- Path: `apps/<domain>/<role>-<name>` (examples: `apps/agenstra/backend-agent-manager`, `apps/forepath/frontend-landingpage`)
- Nx project name: `<domain>-<role>-<name>` (example: `agenstra-backend-agent-manager`)
- Role prefixes: `backend-`, `frontend-`, `native-`, `mcp-`, `keycloak-theme-`

**Domain libraries** (via `lib`):

- Path: `libs/domains/<domain>/<scope>/<type>-<name>` (example: `libs/domains/decabill/backend/feature-billing-manager`)
- Nx project name: `<domain>-<scope>-<type>-<name>`
- Import path: `@forepath/<domain>/<scope>/<type>-<name>`
- Tags: `domain:<domain>,scope:<scope>,type:<type>`

**New domain** (via `domain`):

- Path: `libs/domains/<name>/` with `backend/`, `frontend/`, `keycloak/`, `shared/` index stubs
- Adds `tsconfig.base.json` path aliases and a baseline `domain:<name>` boundary rule

## Recommended order

1. **`domain`** — only when the product domain is new
2. **`lib`** — shared code the new app will depend on
3. **App generator** — `backend`, `frontend`, `mcp`, `keycloak-theme`, or `native` (native requires an existing frontend SSR project)
4. **Verify** — `nx show project <project-name> --json` (buffer per `nx-cli.mdc`), then lint/test affected targets

## `@forepath/code` generators

Run from repository root. Omit options to get interactive prompts.

### `domain`

Creates domain scaffold under `libs/domains/<name>/`.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:domain payments --prefix=@forepath
```

| Option | Required | Default | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|-------|
| `name` | yes | — | Domain folder name |
| `prefix` | no | `@domain` | Package/import prefix root |

### `lib`

Creates a typed library under a domain.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:lib --domain=decabill --scope=backend --type=feature --name=billing-manager --generator=node
```

| Option | Required | Values | Notes |
|--------|----------|--------|-------|
| `domain` | yes | — | Must exist (`domain` generator or prior domain) |
| `scope` | yes | `frontend`, `backend`, `keycloak`, `shared` | Sets `scope:*` tag |
| `type` | yes | `data-access`, `feature`, `ui`, `util` | Sets `type:*` tag |
| `name` | yes | — | Library segment name |
| `generator` | yes | `js`, `node`, `angular` | Base Nx library generator |

Pick `generator=angular` for frontend UI/libs, `node` for Nest/backend libs, `js` for framework-agnostic shared code.

### `backend`

NestJS app at `apps/<domain>/backend-<name>`.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:backend billing-manager --domain=decabill
nx generate @forepath/code:backend public-api --domain=forepath --protected=false
```

| Option | Required | Default | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|-------|
| `name` | yes | — | Without `backend-` prefix |
| `domain` | no | `agenstra` | Product domain |
| `protected` | no | `true` | Authenticated routes |

### `frontend`

Angular app at `apps/<domain>/frontend-<name>`.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:frontend landingpage --domain=forepath --prefix=app --ui=bootstrap
nx generate @forepath/code:frontend portal --domain=agenstra --ui=none --no-ssr
```

| Option | Required | Default | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|-------|
| `name` | yes | — | Without `frontend-` prefix |
| `domain` | no | `agenstra` | Product domain |
| `prefix` | no | `app` | Component/selector prefix |
| `ui` | no | `bootstrap` | `bootstrap` or `none` |
| `protected` | no | `true` | Authenticated routes |
| `localization` | no | `true` | i18n |
| `ssr` | no | `true` | Server-side rendering |

### `native`

Electron desktop app bundling a domain frontend SSR server.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:native agent-console --domain=agenstra
nx generate @forepath/code:native agent-console --domain=agenstra --frontendProject=agenstra-frontend-agent-console
```

| Option | Required | Default | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|-------|
| `name` | yes | — | Without `native-` prefix |
| `domain` | no | `agenstra` | Product domain |
| `frontendProject` | no | `<domain>-frontend-<name>` | Existing frontend Nx project |
| `title` | no | — | Window title |

### `keycloak-theme`

Keycloakify theme at `apps/<domain>/keycloak-theme-<name>`.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:keycloak-theme platform --domain=shared
```

| Option | Required | Default | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|-------|
| `name` | yes | — | Theme name |
| `domain` | no | `shared` | Usually `shared` |
| `prefix` | no | `app` | Component prefix |

### `mcp`

MCP server at `apps/<domain>/mcp-<name>`.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:mcp devkit --domain=shared
```

| Option | Required | Default | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|-------|
| `name` | yes | — | Server name |
| `domain` | no | `shared` | Product domain |
| `protected` | no | `true` | Authenticated routes |

### `init`

One-time repo setup for AI agent structure. No options.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/code:init
```

## `@forepath/ai` generators and executor

### `context`

Validates `.agenstra/` and optionally emits tool configs.

```bash
nx generate @forepath/ai:context --path=. --dryRun
nx generate @forepath/ai:context --path=. --target=cursor,github-copilot --outputDir=generated
```

| Option | Default | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|
| `path` | `.` | Directory containing `.agenstra/` |
| `project` | — | Alternative: Nx project whose root holds `.agenstra/` |
| `target` | all tools | `cursor`, `opencode`, `github-copilot` |
| `outputDir` | `generated` | Output base directory |
| `dryRun` | `false` | Validate only; no write |

### `transform` executor

For projects with an `agenstra-transform` target in `project.json`:

```bash
nx run my-app:agenstra-transform --target=cursor --outputDir=./generated --dryRun
```

Prefer **`dryRun` / `--dryRun`** when validating context changes before writing generated agent files.

## Before and after running

**Before:**

```bash
# Inspect schema (no writes)
nx generate @forepath/code:backend --help

# Optional Nx dry-run preview
nx generate @forepath/code:backend my-api --domain=forepath --dry-run 2>&1 | tee tmp/nx-agent/gen-backend-dry-run.log
```

**After:**

- Read `project.json` and generated tree from disk; do not re-run the generator
- Run `nx show project <project-name> --json` → buffer file
- Implement feature code inside generated boundaries; extend via new `lib` projects rather than duplicating app structure
- Run affected lint/test (see `feature-prototyping.skill.mdc` / `nx-cli.mdc`)

## Anti-patterns (avoid)

- Copying an existing app folder and search-replacing names
- Creating libraries directly with `@nx/angular:library` / `@nx/node:library` without `@forepath/code:lib` (misses tags, paths, domain index exports, boundary rules)
- Picking a `domain` that does not exist and skipping `domain` generator
- Re-running `nx generate` with the same name after partial failure — inspect tree and schema first; delete or fix conflicts manually if needed
- Editing generated boundary rules without understanding cross-domain dependencies (compare with existing domains in `.eslintrc.json`)

## Stop and escalate

- Generator fails mid-run or leaves conflicting files
- Required cross-domain imports are blocked and need architecture approval
- No generator fits the use case (e.g. non-standard deployable)

Stop, capture the generator log in `tmp/nx-agent/`, state what was created, and propose options (extend generator, manual exception with review) rather than silent hand-rolling.
